Question 174) The human resources sector of a company will conduct an interview with 120 candidates for an accountant vacancy. By lot, they intend to attribute a number to each candidate, put the list of numbers in increasing numerical order and use it to summon those interested. It turns out that, by a defect of the computer, numbers with 5 distinct digits were generated and, in none of them, appeared even digits. Because of this, the call order of the candidate who has received the number 75 913
A) 24.
B) 31.
C) 32.
D) 88.
E) 89.
